## Subtitle Pipeline State Fields

The following fields appear on both `short-videos` and `course-subtitle-jobs` (and mirrored into embedded `LessonVideo` on `courses`):

| Field | Description |
|---|---|
| `subtitle_status` | Current state: `pending` → `processing` → `completed` / `failed` |
| `subtitle_failure_reason` | Error message from last failed attempt |
| `subtitle_retry_count` | How many times the worker has attempted this job |
| `last_subtitle_attempt` | Timestamp of the most recent worker pickup |
| `retryable` | Whether the failure is transient (worker may retry) |
| `not_before` | Earliest datetime the worker may process this job (upload delay guard) |

The worker (`src/workers/captionWorker.ts`) polls on a 60-second interval. On first upload, `not_before` is set to `now + 2 minutes` to allow Cloudinary time to finish processing the video before transcription is triggered.
